  "texts": [
    "Theorem 3.12.",
    "For every metric d-current T ∈ P d, we have∥T ∥ P d = ∥T ∥ C(K).In particular, the former quantity is finite.Proof.",
    "The inequality ∥T ∥ P d ≥ ∥T ∥ C(K) is immediate, as the supremum on the left hand side is taken over a larger set.",
    "We show the converse inequality.",
    "Utilizing Corollary 3.3, we obtain∥T ∥ P d = sup ∥ω∥ P d ≤1 |T (ω)| = sup{ i T (f i, π i): s( i (f i, π i)) ≤ 1} = sup{ i T (f i, π i): i ∥f i ∥ L d j=1 Lip(π j i) ≤ 1} ≤ sup{ i ∥T ∥ C(K) ∥f i ∥ L d j=1Lip(π j i):i ∥f i ∥ L d j=1 Lip(π j i) ≤ 1} ≤ ∥T ∥ C(K).Remark 3.13."
